QoS Level	Meaning	Description
QoS 0	At most once	Message is sent only once. No confirmation is received.
QoS 1	At least once	Message is guaranteed to arrive, but it may be delivered more than once.
QoS 2	Exactly once	Message is delivered only once with the highest reliability.
Which QoS is Best for an IoT Water Level Monitoring System?
Answer: QoS 1 (At least once)
Reason:
•	Ensures that important water level data reaches the server. 
•	Slight duplicate messages are acceptable. 
•	Lower overhead than QoS 2. 
•	More reliable than QoS 0. 
•	Commonly used in IoT monitoring applications.
